      "title": "Solve for the output",
      "content": "Isolate $y$ in the equation.<br/>$$\\frac{3}{5}x+\\frac{3}{4}y=8$$<br/>$$\\frac{3}{4}y=8-\\frac{3}{5}x$$<br/>$$y=\\frac{4}{3}(8-\\frac{3}{5}x)$$<br/>$$y=\\frac{32}{3}-\\frac{4}{5}x$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Evaluate the table inputs",
      "content": "Use the listed $x$-values.<br/>$$x=1:\\quad y=\\frac{32}{3}-\\frac{4}{5}=\\frac{148}{15}$$<br/>$$x=2:\\quad y=\\frac{32}{3}-\\frac{8}{5}=\\frac{136}{15}$$<br/>$$x=4:\\quad y=\\frac{32}{3}-\\frac{16}{5}=\\frac{112}{15}$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Match the table",
      "content": "The table with $y$-values $\\frac{148}{15}$, $\\frac{136}{15}$, and $\\frac{112}{15}$ for $x=1$, $x=2$, and $x=4$ is the matching table. The answer is <strong>D</strong>."
